						               													<description>From the makers of Dinner's Ready!, Happy Hour! is the first card game to help get you buzzed, challenging players to collect and deliver cocktails based on actual recipes! Not only is Happy Hour! fun and competitive, the more you play, the more familiar you'll become with cocktails!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    Drinking IS NOT a required element of playing the Happy Hour! card game, but we do have suggested drinking rules for full enjoyment!*&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Happy Hour! is easy to set up and fun to play!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Happy Hour! is a game that fundamentally parallels the bartending experience of assembling mixed drink orders as quickly as possible.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Overview of gameplay: Players are dealt a hand of INGREDIENT CARDS, containing alcohols, mixers, and toppings.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;INGREDIENT CARDS: There are four kinds of alcohol ingredients: vodka, whiskey, gin, and tequila!&amp;#10;There are a handful of MIXERS, including triple sec, sweet &amp;amp; sour, club soda, tonic water, ginger beer and vermouth!&amp;#10;The TOPPING cards consist of garnish (orange/lime/lemon/olive), cherry, and mint!&amp;#10;There are also ACTION CARDS which can help or hinder your drink-making progress, including spilled drinks, restock the bar, &amp;quot;scratch that,&amp;quot; make it a double, and wild cards!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;THE BAR: A row of ingredient cards available during each turn.&amp;#10;THE COUNTER: A row of recipe cards that must be fulfilled.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Using these cards in combination, players can create any one of the 21 drink RECIPE CARDS. Drinks range on a scale of 4-7 points, depending on quantity of ingredients required.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The first &amp;quot;bartender&amp;quot; to collect 21 points wins!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Happy Hour! is a fun card game for 2-4 adults, with rounds typically requiring 10-40 minutes.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
